Reasoning: The paper deals with the Sherali-Adams refutation system and the binary encoding of combinatorial principles, which are topics related to computational complexity (cs.CC) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The use of binary encoding also suggests a connection to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The study of rank and size of refutations is related to proof complexity (cs.LO). Finally, the application of these concepts to the SA-Lasserre refutation system suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
